    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00/3–146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kyle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-01T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >March 1, 1946—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:29 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. On February 28 Foreign Minister<note n="92" xml:id="d198fn92">Guillermo
                        Toreillo.</note> said he had finished study Blue Book on Argentina which he
                    found “formidable” and which left no doubt of complicity Perón-Farrell regime as
                    distinct from Argentine people. He observed that important matter now is what
                    steps will be taken should Perón win election and hoped election of Tamborini
                    would open way to Argentine participation at Rio.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kyle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
